  * New upstream release
  * Updated patches 23-vary-invalidation, 26-vary_options, 20-wikimedia-errors
  * Updated the rules file to install logfile-daemon

 -- Mark Bergsma <mark@wikimedia.org>  Tue, 27 Jan 2009 17:30:32 +0000

squid (2.6.18-1wm2) gutsy; urgency=low

  * Added X-Vary-Options feature. Replaces 22-normalize-requestAE.dpatch .

 -- Tim Starling <tstarling@wikimedia.org>  Thu, 07 Feb 2008 22:23:58 +1100

squid (2.6.18-1wm1) edgy; urgency=high

  * New upstream release
    - Remove patch 24-httpheader-repacking; integrated upstream
    - Includes fix for new security bug introduced by this patch
  * Accept-Encoding request header normalization by Domas Mituzas
    <domas@wikimedia.org>
    - Take out 21-nomanglerequestheaders
    - Include 21-nomangle-requestCC which only prevents Cache-Control request
      header mangling
    - Include 22-normalize-requestAE which normalizes the Accept-Encoding
      request header to only two distinct cases: gzipped, or not

 -- Mark Bergsma <mark@wikimedia.org>  Sun, 13 Jan 2008 15:51:11 +0000

squid (2.6.16-1wm1) edgy; urgency=medium

  * New upstream release 2.6.STABLE16
    - Drop patch 23-storedir-minobjsize, now integrated upstream
    - Drop patch 01-cf.debian, conflicts with upstream changes and serves
      no purpose for Wikimedia use
  * Add a build dependencies on libgoogle-perftools-dev, debhelper and
    devscripts
  * Include HTTP header array repacking patch by Adrian Chadd

 -- Mark Bergsma <mark@wikimedia.org>  Mon, 19 Nov 2007 10:40:15 +0000

